    <abstract id="aspace_6517ed04be91d80141d4d41df4ceb828">The Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences serves as New York University's mathematics research school. It grew from the Graduate School of Arts and Science's Department of Mathematics starting in 1935, when Richard Courant joined the faculty. It was named the Institute for Mathematics and Mechanics in 1946.  The Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences (CIMS) Library, located in Warren Weavevr Hall, supported the Institute's research and teaching in the fields of data science, mathematics, and computer science. The CIMS Library ceased operations in 2023, transferring information resources and services to other libraries within NYU. The Records of the Courant Institute Library (dated 1955-2000) consists of administrative records documenting the operations of the Library, and include correspondence, reports, policies, and collections of clippings.</abstract>
    <physloc id="aspace_7cac98ca61c2bbba69f00cdbb4456f6a" label="Location Note">Materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please request materials at least two business days prior to your research visit to coordinate access.</physloc>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_da6e83426167cf03c6e86c6a485f210b">Materials are in English.</langmaterial>
  </did>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_cde290293e3698fe1288a02ddc27524f">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>The Records of the Courant Institute Library (dated 1955-2000) consists of administrative records documenting the operations of the Library, and include correspondence, reports, policies, and collections of clippings.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <arrangement id="aspace_e4b93a67d26898970b40e94765a88217">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>Files are arranged alphabetically.</p>  </arrangement>
  <bioghist id="aspace_9b38eaf8ac280a0b344485086506d193">
    <head>Historical Note</head>
<p>The Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences serves as New York University's mathematics research school. It grew from the Graduate School of Arts and Science's Department of Mathematics starting in 1935, when Richard Courant joined the faculty. It was named the Institute for Mathematics and Mechanics in 1946.  The Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences (CIMS) Library, located in Warren Weavevr Hall, supported the Institute's research and teaching in the fields of data science, mathematics, and computer science. The CIMS Library ceased operations in 2023, transferring information resources and services to other libraries within NYU.</p>  </bioghist>
  <accessrestrict id="aspace_7666980942c941fb6e63029b9da2e206">
    <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
<p>Materials are open without restrictions.</p>  </accessrestrict>
  <userestrict id="aspace_080010054818c65d359ba3d56becb4b4">
    <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
<p>Any rights (including copyright and related rights to publicity and privacy) held by Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences Library are maintained by New York University. Permission to publish or reproduce materials in this collection must be secured from the repository. Please contact NYU Special Collections, special.collections@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.</p>  </userestrict>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_1fc65c2433301355568b03edf4b812a4">
    <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
<p>Transferred from the Courant Institute in the summer of 2023 when the Courant Institute Library closed. The accession number associated with this transfer is 2026.016.</p>  </acqinfo>
  <prefercite id="aspace_ec68de88cdc040548c0224c01b339b2f">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>Identification of item, date; Records of the Courant Institute Library; RG 38.10; box number; folder number or item identifier; New York University Archives, New York University.</p>  </prefercite>
  <processinfo id="aspace_f6ee2bca17e8959b4874d7fd44801320">
    <head>Processing Information</head>
<p>At the time of accessioning, materials were rehoused in archival boxes and folders, arranged alphabetically, described on the collection-level, and inventoried at the folder-level.</p>  </processinfo>
  <appraisal id="aspace_b0ca0ca96b8c331ce2f5c820cb785ada">
    <head>Appraisal</head>
<p>Personnel files, newspaper clippings about NYU generally, and reports already present in the New York University Archives holdings were appraised out of the collection during acquisition.</p>  </appraisal>
